  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Sustainable Co-existence and Healthy Living Conditions in Kono District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Communities will be sensitized to be knowledgeable about their entitlements/rights. They will be trained and organized to demand accountability and transparency from service providers and give feedback.   Feedback from the communities will be obtained for example by using a community score card to determine the level of satisfaction with the health services provision in targeted communities. Poor and marginalized people will participate in town hall meetings and serve as direct beneficiaries of the project.  Information generated from communities in terms of their priorities, aspiration and concerns will be disseminated through the print and electronic media for learning and sharing. 
The project will further train and orientate community CHMVGs, CAGs on how to identify and support community Development initiatives.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved transparency and accountability at district level with increased capacity of community people to hold their duty bearers to account.</narrative>
  </description>
